choices.text:
without question the massive influx of skilled labor workers from China in the late 1990's. These migrants have transformed Gabon. They built the gas fields and the road network of Gabon. They transformed Libreville, the country's capital city, into the concrete jungle that we see today.

150 Chinese companies are supplying goods through the Chinese Government Export Promotion Company [GEXPTEC]. Chinese universities are providing technical training to Gendarmerie and Navy personnel. High Schools such as the Laauder English High School are being run by the Chinese authorities. Chinese sports associations take part every year at the L’Oranie Cup, at organising the sports days at school [1999, 2005]. They run militarised help to combat problems of wildlife trafficking. In addition – and this is what differentiates the Chinese from the others including the French: they also bring their cultural ideas about social distribution into these projects with communities and autarcic experiences…

I participated every year in the yearly China-Africa business conference or the China-Africa Forum organised by the Beijing New Star Bridge [an organisation that promotes the study and development of Africa within China], where many Chinese are asking how to come and invest in Africa... message I would never expect from the French. Moreover, these discussions take place in the West, at the heart of African political and intellectual centres, protestation of 'new imperialism' is found not in those centres but in peripheral Xia Shanguo’s, resolutely perip
